subsection.p:
 			Consider a uniformly charged cylinder with volume charge density

 				\rho = \begin{cases}
			 			\rho_0 \amp 0\le s \le R\\
			 			0 \amp s \gt R.
			 			\end{cases}

 			The magnitude of electric field varies with distance by two different rules, one for points inside the sphere and another for point outside the sphere as we will derive below.

 				E = \begin{cases}
			 			 \dfrac{\rho_0}{2\epsilon_0}\, s\amp  0\le s \le R,\\
			 			\dfrac{\rho_0}{2\epsilon_0}\, \dfrac{R^2}{s}\amp   s \gt R.
			 			\end{cases}

 			 shows a drawing of this function.
